<body>
    <div id="container">
    <a class="header" href="welcome"><h1>IndieCert</h1></a>
    <p class="warn">
This is currently an <strong>EXPERIMENTAL</strong> service!
    </p>

    <p>
IndieCert is a service to authenticate to services around the web without
using usernames and passwords. IndieCert uses client certificates installed
in the user's browser. Client certificates provide superior security. Until
now it has been cumbersome to deploy client certificates outside managed
corporate environments. This service improves on
this by making it easier to deploy client certificates and support multiple
(mobile) devices.
    </p>
    <p class="info">
For more information you are kindly invited to look at the technical
description in
<a href="https://www.tuxed.net/fkooman/blog/indiecert.html">this</a> blog
entry.
    </p>
    <p>
All <a href="https://github.com/fkooman/indiecert">code</a> is available under
the <a href="https://gnu.org/licenses/agpl.html">AGPLv3</a> license. There are
also Docker
<a href="https://github.com/fkooman/indiecert/tree/master/docker">instructions</a>
for easily running your own instance!
    </p>

    <h2>Relying Party?</h2>
    <p>
Check out the relying party <a href="rp">instructions</a>!
    </p>

    <h2>Try It!</h2>
    <p>
Here you can try out IndieCert! You will be guided through generating a client
certificate and adding the fingerprint to your home page! Please enter a domain
name or URL to a page you can modify. It <strong>MUST</strong> be reachable over HTTPS!
    </p>

    <form method="get" action="auth">
    <input type="hidden" name="redirect_uri" value="{{ redirect_uri|e }}">
    <input type="text" name="me" id="me" placeholder="yourdomain.com">
    <input type="submit" value="Sign In">
    </form>
    <p>
You can check the <a href="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</a>.
    </p>
    
    <div class="footer">
        <a href="faq">FAQ</a> | IndieCert
    </div>

    </div>
</body>
</html>
